# MY_Project Structure and Claude Skill Usage

This document summarizes the folder structure of the project and provides instructions for using each skill and agent in Claude / Claude Code CLI.

---

## Project Structure
MY_Project/
├── CLAUDE.MD # Project guide, instructions
├── MEMORY.MD # memory, and shortcuts
├── agents/ # Task-specific agents
│ ├── proofreader.md # Proofreading agent
│ └── ...
├── skills/ # Workflow controllers
│ ├── proofread.md # Generic proofread skill for Word/LaTeX/Quarto
│ ├── review-paper.md # Manuscript review skill
│ ├── lit-review.md # Literature review skill
│ └── create-slides.md # Slide creation skill
├── papers/ # Source manuscripts / notes (.docx, .tex, .pdf, .qmd)
├── output/ # Generated drafts (slides, Quarto drafts, figures)
├── quality_reports/ # Proofread reports, review logs, plans, literature reviews
├── templates/ # Report templates, notation registry
└── scripts/ # Optional automation scripts (e.g., batch processing)


---

## Skill & Agent Usage in Claude / Claude Code CLI

### 1. `/proofread` — Proofreading Documents

```bash
# Single file
/proofread papers/example.docx

# Batch process all files
/proofread all

### 2. `/review-paper` — Manuscript / Paper Review
# Review a specific manuscript
/review-paper papers/my_paper.docx

# Review LaTeX or PDF
/review-paper papers/research_note.tex

### 3. ` /lit-review ` — Literature Search and Synthesis
# Review a research topic
/lit-review "climate risk and corporate finance"

# Use a specific paper title or research question
/lit-review "Fama-French 3-factor model"

### 4. ` /create-slides`  — Slide Creation Workflow
# Create slides for a topic
/create-slides "Climate Risk Lecture"

# Use a source paper as input
/create-slides papers/climate_risk_paper.docx

### 5. Batch Processing Example
#!/usr/bin/env bash
# scripts/batch_proofread.sh

PROJECT_DIR="/Users/my/Desktop/Claude/MY Project"
PAPERS_DIR="$PROJECT_DIR/papers"

for docx_file in "$PAPERS_DIR"/*.docx; do
  echo "Processing $docx_file ..."
  claude /proofread "$docx_file"
done
